==English==
===Noun===
'''petit mal''' 

Etymology: from the French for Little Illness.

#A form of [[epilepsy]] where the [[seizure]]s are characterized as minor, the person become vacant or unaware but not involving [[spasm]]s and [[unconsciousness]].  These seizures are usually brief, lasting up to 30 seconds, and may include [[twitching]]. A formal medical term would be [[absence seizures]]. 

*Contrast [[petit mal]] seizures.

